Film4.uk.title: S.W.A.T.
Film4.uk.description: (2003) Action with Colin Farrell and Samuel L Jackson. A loose canon joins an elite force to escort a fugitive to chokey. But the baddie's put a reward out for help with his escape.

Film4.uk.title: The Long Good Friday
Film4.uk.description: (1980) Bob Hoskins and Helen Mirren star in John MacKenzie's East London gangster thriller. Gang leader Hoskins' hold over his empire is under threat.

Film4.uk.title: Chopper
Film4.uk.description: (2000) Darkly comic, quasi-true crime biopic starring Eric Bana as notorious Australian criminal Mark 'Chopper' Read who, among other things, got a fellow inmate to chop off his ears.

Film4.uk.title: Teleshopping
Film4.uk.description: Teleshopping.

Film4.uk.title: Teleshopping
Film4.uk.description: Teleshopping.

Film4.uk.title: Picnic
Film4.uk.description: (1955) William Holden and Kim Novak star in this sweltering tale of deception, betrayal and illicit love in small-town Kansas.

Film4.uk.title: Arizona Raiders
Film4.uk.description: (1965) William Whitney's brutal western. Two former Confederate rebels are offered their freedom if they can track, catch or even kill their former gang mates. Starring Audie Murphy.

Film4.uk.title: Hangman's Knot
Film4.uk.description: (1952) Civil War-era Western. A unit of Confederate soldiers attack a Union troop to steal gold. Learning that the war is over, they must finish the mission in disguise.

Film4.uk.title: The Blue Lamp
Film4.uk.description: (1950) Gritty noir thriller from Ealing Studios. A rookie PC hunts a vicious killer across blitz-battered London. With Jimmy Hanley, Dirk Bogarde and Jack Warner as PC George Dixon.

Film4.uk.title: Film4 Interview Programmes:...
Film4.uk.description: ...Talking Film: Stars and directors talk about making movies in this compendium of personal and practical reflections. Features Danny Boyle, Amy Schumer, Chiwetel Ejiofor and more.

Film4.uk.title: Hunter Killer
Film4.uk.description: (2018) Nautical action thriller. Gerard Butler stars as an unconventional submarine skipper sent to investigate the torpedoing of a US vessel. With Gary Oldman, Linda Cardellini and Common.

Film4.uk.title: Transporter 2
Film4.uk.description: (2005) Violent action-thriller starring Jason Statham as the tough courier Frank Martin, who's hired to guard a government drugs czar's son. But his mission soon lurches towards disaster.

Film4.uk.title: xXx
Film4.uk.description: (2002) Action thriller starring Vin Diesel as Xander Cage: a thrill-seeking extreme sports enthusiast, stuntman and rebellious athlete-turned-reluctant spy. With Samuel L Jackson.

Film4.uk.title: xXx: The Next Level
Film4.uk.description: (2005) Action thriller sequel with Samuel L Jackson and Ice Cube. There's a new Triple X agent in town and he's up against some shady government business. Violence.

Film4.uk.title: Teleshopping
Film4.uk.description: Teleshopping.

Film4.uk.title: Teleshopping
Film4.uk.description: Teleshopping.

Film4.uk.title: The Last Hurrah
Film4.uk.description: (1958) Satirical, political drama with Spencer Tracy. Ruthless mayor Frank Skeffington seeks re-election for the fifth and final time. But have his old tactics run their course?

Film4.uk.title: A Lawless Street
Film4.uk.description: (1955) A non-stop romp of a western from director Joseph H Lewis. In the town of Medicine Bend, only Marshal Calem Ware can keep its citizens from falling into complete lawlessness.

Film4.uk.title: The Admirable Crichton
Film4.uk.description: (1957) Comedy. Kenneth More stars as the perfect butler, who assumes command when he, his aristocratic employer (Cecil Parker) and his family and friends are shipwrecked on a desert island.

Film4.uk.title: Gift Horse
Film4.uk.description: (1952) War drama. Trevor Howard plays the captain of an ageing US warship, gifted to the British navy, which is chosen to lead the raid on Saint-Nazaire in 1942. With Richard Attenborough.

Film4.uk.title: Enemy Mine
Film4.uk.description: (1985) Sci-fi adventure starring Dennis Quaid and Louis Gossett Jr. A human and his alien enemy find themselves stranded alone on a hostile planet, where they must work together to survive.

Film4.uk.title: Inglourious Basterds
Film4.uk.description: (2009) Quentin Tarantino's World War II action-adventure. Jewish American soldiers go Nazi-hunting in occupied France. With Brad Pitt, Diane Kruger, Christoph Waltz and Michael Fassbender.

Film4.uk.title: Freaky
Film4.uk.description: (2020) Body-swap comedy horror with Vince Vaughn. A girl gets murdered by a serial killer but then wakes up in his body, with only 24 hours to get her own body back!

Film4.uk.title: Deerskin
Film4.uk.description: (2019) Comedy horror. A middle-aged man (Jean Dujardin) buys a deerskin jacket to kick off his post-divorce life. Fine - until the jacket starts talking to him...

Film4.uk.title: Teleshopping
Film4.uk.description: Teleshopping.

Film4.uk.title: Teleshopping
Film4.uk.description: Teleshopping.

Film4.uk.title: Barnacle Bill
Film4.uk.description: (1957) The final Ealing comedy stars Alec Guinness as the latest in a long and distinguished line of sailors, but there's a problem: he suffers from seasickness. So why not buy a pier?

Film4.uk.title: Yesterday's Enemy
Film4.uk.description: (1959) Wartime drama with Stanley Baker. The captain of a British army patrol deciphers secret enemy battle plans, but does so at a great moral cost.

Film4.uk.title: It Should Happen to You
Film4.uk.description: (1954) Judy Holliday stars in this comedy as a smalltown girl who comes to New York and rents a billboard to publicise her name - and soon she's a TV star. With Jack Lemmon.

Film4.uk.title: Film4 Interview Programmes:...
Film4.uk.description: ...Talking Film: Stars and directors talk about making movies in this compendium of personal and practical reflections. Features Danny Boyle, Amy Schumer, Chiwetel Ejiofor and more.

Film4.uk.title: Mysterious Island
Film4.uk.description: (1961) Sci-fi adventure based on Jules Verne's novel. Two men fleeing the US Civil War find an island inhabited by monsters (animated by Ray Harryhausen) and the mysterious Captain Nemo.

Film4.uk.title: Notting Hill
Film4.uk.description: (1999) Hugh Grant and Julia Roberts star in the BAFTA-winning comedy romance about a bookshop owner who manages to get a glamorous movie star to go out with him. With Rhys Ifans.

Film4.uk.title: Nobody
Film4.uk.description: (2021) Action thriller with Bob Odenkirk. He's just a dad who goes to work and takes out the trash. But really he's an ex-assassin about to unleash his true self... and take out the trash.

Film4.uk.title: Ghost Rider
Film4.uk.description: (2007) Nicolas Cage is Marvel's soul-hunting, hot-headed-biker antihero. When Mephistopheles's son starts causing trouble in hell, Ghost Rider is forced to sort it out. With Peter Fonda.

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: War Factories
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: The People's Car: While America had Ford or Chrysler or Buick, Hitler also wanted a car that would transform his nation: the 'people's car'- a Volkswagen. S2 Ep3

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: The World at War
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Pincers: Laurence Olivier provides the narration to this World War II retrospective. Hear how 1944 saw the steady disintegration of the German war machine, as the Allies advanced. S1 Ep19

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: Antiques Roadshow
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Retrospective 2: Fiona Bruce introduces more items from the show's visits to Hutton-in-the-Forest, Chatsworth and the British Museum. S33 Ep29

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: Canal Boat Diaries
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Braunston to Lapworth: Robbie Cumming journeys through Royal Leamington Spa and the historic town of Warwick with its medieval castle. S5 Ep1

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: Bangers & Cash
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: 1961 Morris Minor 1000: Paul and Jack head to Staffordshire to pick up five vehicles from collector Rob's colossal barn, including a Mini and a Morris Minor. S8 Ep3

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: Flipping Bangers
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Austin Maestro: Gus and Will go for the once-maligned Austin Maestro. The car they want to buy has already been sold but the seller has another - his own - on the driveway. Can they do a deal? S2 Ep3

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: Bangers & Cash
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Swift/Toyota Corona/Bedford Van: Derek goes to pick up a veteran 1904 Swift, there's an emotional farewell to a 1980s Bedford HA van, and a Toyota Corona finds a new home. S9 Ep4

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: Bangers & Cash
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Ford Granada/Toyota Hilux: Derek navigates the dry stone walls of the Peak District to collect a very original 1988 Opel Manta. Plus, Dave deals with a Ford Granada rally support vehicle. S6 Ep4

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: Bangers & Cash
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Bedford Bus/Triumph TR7: Derek has a three-hour drive in a 1960s bus that arrived in the UK after a life in the sun. Dave takes a Triumph TR7 convertible to auction. S6 Ep5

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: Abandoned Engineering
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Lost Bridges: Hear about some magnificent bridges that time forgot. A hurricane put paid to Goat Canyon Trestle in California, while Kinzua Viaduct was destroyed by a tornado. S1 Ep3

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: Great British Railway Journeys
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Tilbury to Barbican: Michael Portillo travels from London's Docklands to the Barbican, examining the story of the arrival at Tilbury in 1948 of over a thousand passengers from the Caribbean. S14 Ep6

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: Great British Railway Journeys
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Waterloo to Regent's Park: Michael Portillo visits London's South Bank, where the 1951 Festival of Britain drew more than eight and a half million visitors. S14 Ep7

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: Great British Railway Journeys
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Paddington to Ongar: Michael Portillo ventures deep underground onto London's newest railway - the Elizabeth Line - enjoying a smooth ride from Paddington to Tottenham Court Road. S14 Ep8

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: Great British Railway Journeys
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Felixstowe to Norwich: Michael Portillo explores Felixstowe, which suffered catastrophic flooding in 1953, and in Norwich, he admires the Norman Cathedral. S14 Ep9

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: Bangers & Cash
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Vanden Plas/Ford Fiesta XR2: Dave's on his way to Grimsby to pick up an iconic 80s fast Ford, the Mk1 Fiesta XR2. S6 Ep6

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: Bangers & Cash
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Alvis 12/50/Alfetta/RS2000: Derek gets a tour of Hadlow Castle in Kent when he arrives to collect the owner's pre-war Alvis and an immaculate Citroen used by the Gestapo in occupied France. S6 Ep7

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: War Factories
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Apocalypse Factories: The incredible story of the arms race to create America's nuclear arms factories. S2 Ep4

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: The World at War
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Genocide: How did Heinrich Himmler plan to realise Hitler's vision of a pure Aryan Germany? Actor Laurence Olivier explains as he narrates the acclaimed documentary series about WWII. S1 Ep20

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: Antiques Roadshow
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Hampton Court Castle 1: Fiona Bruce and the experts visit Hampton Court Castle in Herefordshire, where items include an heirloom from the early days of photography. S33 Ep15

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: Antiques Roadshow
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Dartmouth 1: The team visits the Britannia Royal Naval College in Dartmouth, Devon, where items up for valuation include a relic from HMS Victory. S33 Ep16

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Thunderbird / Citroen SM / Punto / BMW: Derek travels to the Lancashire coast to pick up a rare 1972 Citroen SM, and Dave admires a two-decade-old Punto with just 42 miles on the clock. S9 Ep6

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Ferrari Rep/Figaro/3 Tractors: Derek is on the road to pick up a funky little Nissan Figaro and a sublime Ferrari 250 GT tribute car, and Paul gets to try out his spanking new Scania T Cab. S9 Ep7

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: Porridge
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Happy Release: A broken ankle provides Fletcher with a spell in the prison hospital, along with a fellow patient (David Jason) who mentions a hidden eight grand. Classic laughs. S2 Ep5

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: Porridge
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: The Harder They Fall: Ageless comedy with Ronnie Barker behind bars at Slade. Godber enters the prison boxing championships, and although he is the hot favourite, he must lose. S2 Ep6
